Aloha Senate President Kouchi and Speaker Nakamura:
An arbitration award has been issued concerning the Hawai'i Firefighters Association
collective bargaining (CB) for Unit 11 (Firefighters). The award was issued on
March 30, 2026. In accordance with Section 89-11, HRS, cost items must be submitted
to the Legislature for appropriation. The following is a summary of the included and
excluded requirements of the award for the current fiscal biennium which are being
transmitted to the Legislature for authorization:
FY 26 FY 27 Biennium
Salaries & Fringe
General $ 232,989 $ 492,689 $ 725,678
Special 909,597 1,923,340 2,832,937
Total $1,142,586 $2,416,029 $3,558,615
In addition, Hawai'i Employer-Union Health Benefits Trust Fund amounts are as follows:
FY 26 FY 27 Biennium
General $231,046 $455,925 $686,971

The Honorable Ronald D. Kouchi
The Honorable Nadine K. Nakamura
April 9, 2026
Page Two of Two
Estimated costs for the third and fourth years of the agreement are also provided for
your reference:
FY 28 FY 29 Biennium
Salaries & Fringe
General $ 717,798 $ 946,338 $1,664,136
Special 2,801,921 3,694,027 6,495,948
Total $3,519,719 $4,640,365 $8,160,084
Attached is a proposed draft House Bill No. 2272, H.D. 1, S.D. 1, G.D. 1, which has
been updated to reflect estimated CB amounts.
Mahala,
